article.headline: Villanova 49, Georgia State 24
article.story: ATLANTA -- John Robertson passed for two touchdowns and ran for another and Kevin Monangai's 130 yards paced the Villanova rushing attack in a 49-24 win over Georgia State on Saturday. The Wildcats led 35-10 at halftime and 49-10 with 13:57 remaining in the first meeting between the Colonial Athletic Association teams. Villanova (6-2, 4-1) finished with 343 yards on 53 carries compared to 79 yards rushing for Georgia State (1-7, 1-4), which lost Donald Russell to a left-knee injury late in the first quarter. Russell, coming off a school-record 201 yards last week against Rhode Island in the Panthers' only victory, had just 4 yards on five carries. He will be evaluated Sunday. Robertson had 11 carries and 11 throws, with eight completions. Monangai, with 18 carries including a 12-yard TD, surpassed 100 yards for the fourth time this season. Poppy Livers returned a Georgia State punt 66 yards to score.
